CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 23, 1945, pg. 9, reads: "FOLKS GATHER 'ROUND THE TABLES at the YMHA, June 14, to make the Student Aid Committee of the Urban Leagues' card party a tremendous success. Shown discussing the affair in first picture are Atty. Thomas Barton, president of the Pittsburgh branch of the league, Dr. Lawrence Greenburger, chairman of the Student Aid Committee, and Miss Toki Schalk, general chairman of the card party..... - Courier Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Atty. Thomas Barton, Dr. Lawrence Greenburger, and Toki Schalk (Johnson), seated in YMHA for card party benefiting the Student Aid Committee of the Urban League
